AI-Powered Fraud Prevention & Trust System
Delivery Partner Trust & Fraud Detection Workflow
Delivery platforms today face serious fraud problems such as fake GPS locations, multiple account
misuse, and cloned applications. In many cases, a single user can act as multiple delivery partners
at the same time and generate fake earnings. This leads to financial losses and can even damage
the reliability of the platform. To solve this issue, we propose an AI-powered system that checks
multiple signals together instead of depending on only one factor like GPS.
The system works through multiple layers to ensure accurate detection. First, it checks device
integrity by identifying fake GPS usage, emulator devices, rooted phones, and cloned apps. Next, it
uses behavioral AI to study patterns like speed, delivery routes, and working hours. Unusual
patterns such as unrealistic movement, repeated loops, or continuous 24/7 activity are flagged. It
also detects multiple accounts operated from the same device by analyzing device fingerprints and
usage similarity.
Based on all these inputs, a Trust Score is assigned to each user between 0 and 100. A high score
allows normal activity, a medium score leads to monitoring, a low score results in restrictions, and a
very low score triggers verification. This scoring system ensures that decisions are fair and based
on multiple factors rather than a single mistake.
To protect genuine users, the system follows a fairness-based approach. Instead of banning users
immediately, it applies gradual actions such as monitoring, restricting, and then verifying. It also
considers real-world problems like poor network connectivity, GPS errors, and device limitations,
reducing false positives.
Key Features of the System:
• Multi-layered fraud detection ensures higher accuracy.
• AI-based behavioral analysis detects patterns that tools cannot hide.
• Trust score system provides transparent and fair decision-making.
• Strong protection against coordinated fraud attacks.
• Fairness layer prevents genuine users from being wrongly penalized.
• Scalable design suitable for large delivery platforms
